column1: **Legend**
* Marine mooring data provided by King County are preliminary and have not received final approval
* Real-time automatic checks are done to determine if values are outside of sensor ranges or if data are missing
column2: and further data review is performed by data managers on a semi-annual basis.

column1: * Inaccuracies in the data may be present because of instrument malfunctions.
* Subsequent review may result in significant revisions to the data.
* Data users are cautioned to consider carefully the provisional nature of this data before using it for decisions.
* Prior to using data in publications and for appropriate citation
column2: contact the Marine and Sediment Assessment Group (MarineWQ@kingcounty.gov).

column1: * ----PARAMETERS---
* Site uses SBE HydroCat-EP sondes for water data. Previously
column2: YSI 6600 V2 sondes were used. The sonde type and unique identifier is stored under ‘Sonde_ID’ column. Meteorological data use Vaisala WXT510 stations.

column1: * There are two sondes at the Seattle Aquarium site: at approximately 1 m and 10 m depths. The sondes are distinguished in the column header by the number at the end of the parameter name (1 = 1 m
* Meteorological data are no longer available at this site beginning March 14
* Parameter names denote measurement unit. Parameters ending in V represent raw voltage values or battery volts.
* For more details
* Site coordinates: Lat 47.60786
* ----QUALIFIER CODES----
* Data for each parameter are followed by a 3-digit qualifier column (where the parameter name is preceded by Qual_). The quality and level of quality control (QC) is denoted for each data value.
*  Summary Qualifier – 1st digit - Denotes status and overall quality of data.
* <1 . . > Finalized – Good – passed secondary review by data manager.
* <2 . . > Provisional – Good – passed initial automatic quality control check.
* <3 . . > Questionable/suspect data. Use data with much caution.
* <4 . . > Poor/bad data. Avoid using this data.
* <9 . . > Missing data.
* Primary Qualifier – 2nd digit – Automatic QC flag.
* <. 0 . > Quality unknown for parameter. Avoid using this data without further review.
* <. 1 . > Passed automatic quality control checks.
* <. 2 . > Sensor failed end check validation after recovery.
* <. 3 . > Value is outside of climatological range by site.
* <. 4 . > Value is outside of measurement range for sensor.
* <. 9 . > Missing data.
* Secondary Qualifier – 3rd digit – Manually applied QC flag after data review by data manager.
* <. . 0> No secondary review completed – Default value.
* <. . 1> Good data
* <. . 2> Probably good data
